Title:
Unauthorized Access to EEO Payroll Groups via Response Tampering

Description:
An unauthorized external user can exploit response tampering to view, modify, delete, and add payroll groups in the EEO Payroll Groups functionality. This vulnerability exposes sensitive payroll information, compromises data integrity, and enables unauthorized actions, posing significant security and compliance risks.

Recommendation:
Input Validation: Validate and sanitize all user inputs and responses from the client side to prevent unauthorized modifications.
Access Control Enforcement: Implement strict server-side authorization checks to ensure that only users with proper permissions can access or modify payroll groups.
Token Validation: Use secure, tamper-proof session tokens to validate user permissions for each request.
Audit Logging: Log all actions performed on payroll groups to identify unauthorized activities promptly.
Periodic Testing: Conduct regular security testing, including response tampering scenarios, to identify and mitigate similar vulnerabilities.
CVSS Score:
CVSS v3.1: 8.2 (High)

Attack Vector (AV): Network (N)
Attack Complexity (AC): Low (L)
Privileges Required (PR): None (N)
User Interaction (UI): Required (R)
Scope (S): Unchanged (U)
Confidentiality (C): High (H)
Integrity (I): High (H)
Availability (A): Low (L)
Steps to Reproduce:
Log in as an unauthorized external user.
Intercept a request related to the EEO Payroll Groups functionality using a proxy tool (e.g., Burp Suite).
Modify the intercepted response to bypass client-side restrictions.
Add, delete, or modify payroll group data using tampered requests.
Observe the changes in the application, confirming unauthorized access and actions.
